itunesNotes.standard: Working out regularly is great, but good health truly begins in the kitchen. This visually dazzling app offers dozens of meal ideas in clever categories like low-carb lunches and post-exercise snacks. Brilliant photos and simple instructions make these recipes easy to follow even for novice chefs, and the built-in shopping list groups items together by grocery-store aisle for shopping efficiency. Now all we need is an app that forces us to hit the gym.

itunesNotes.standard: Food waste is one of the great challenges of our time. Too Good to Go is one way to contribute to a solution. The app provides an overview of shops and restaurants in your area that have surplus food. Those outlets put together a surprise bag at a lower price, and you can order it right within the app. This way, you can protect the environment and discover new places at the same time.
itunesNotes.short: Don’t let your leftover food end up in the bin.

itunesNotes.standard: Plant Jammer helps you answer the question: “What am I going to cook today?“ This is not just a regular recipe app — by using artificial intelligence, it creates dishes that use all the leftovers in your refrigerator. You can even choose to focus on vegetable or healthy recipes. Thanks to simple icons for food selection and variations of each dish, Plant Jammer is an easy tool to minimize your food waste.
